Free Covid19 Testing Sponsored by American Red Cross and Yavapai County Community Health Services

Testing hours date/time:
Saturday Sept 12, 2020 at 7am- 1pm
Sunday Sept 13, 2020 at 1pm - 7pm

Location:
Mingus Union High School - East Parking lot
1801 East Fir Street
Cottonwood, AZ 86326

This free test involves an easy, painless, self-administered nasal swab in a drive-thru stall. Results will be available within 2-4 days from the time specimens arrive at the lab and individuals will receive results through an online portal.

Yavapai county residents can pre-register at https://doineedacovid19test.com/Cottonwood_AZ_1216.html

post_text:
MUHS Leadership is really grateful to be able to host a blood drive on September 30 from 8am - 1pm. Blood drives are deemed an essential service, but have had major reductions in drives and donors due to the pandemic so we are really happy to be able to help in this time. Vitalant is offering FREE COVID ANTI-BODY TESTING with every donation. All safety guidelines will be in place during the drive and masks are required for everyone. Advance appointments are encouraged, visit BloodHero.com (Sponsor Code: Mingus) to schedule an appointment.

Fun Fact: Vitalant supplies blood for ALL hospitals in the state with the exception of 3 in the Tucson area, so your blood could end up back here saving the life of someone in our community!

Arizona State University, Northern Arizona University, and the University of Arizona are coming together to ensure you and your family are well informed about the opportunities and resources available to you. As your public universities, we are working together to ensure you find your best college fit. We are excited to invite you to Tri-University Week https://visit.asu.edu/tri-university

We have teamed up to host joint virtual information sessions for prospective students and families to discuss the following:

How to navigate the college admission process.
Scholarships and financial aid.
Information about each university.
The honors experience at each university.
Don't miss this event occurring on September 8, 9, and 12. We hope you will join us!

Did you know MUHS has a Hope Center?

The Hope Center, located in Mingus Union High School, provides school supplies, clothing, toiletries, food, and household items for ANY student enrolled at our high school.

The Hope Center accepts donation and some items needed are: School Supplies, Men's & Women's clothing, Cleaning Supplies, Toiletries & Gift Cards.

If you would like to help our students, please contact Kristie Seekins, Family & Community Outreach Coordinator at kseekins@muhs.com to schedule a time to drop off items and learn more about our upcoming projects.

https://app.schoolconnectaz.com/service_projects/2519

Hello Mingus Marauders!

We are so excited to welcome you to the 2020-21 school year! Tomorrow is our first day of school and while things may look a little different this year, some things remain the same like Marauder Pride, Marauder Spirit, and Marauder Success. You should have received information from your Advisory teacher about logging into Google Classroom and Edgenuity. We are all here ready to support you and walk alongside you throughout this distance learning experience.

We will "see" you online tomorrow for your first day of school!

Welcome back, Marauders!!

MUHS Families ~

Please complete and submit the 2020/2021 registration enrollment packet to Mingus Union High School see link below and on our website at www.mingusunion.com

*You can submit by scanning and emailing documents to: enrollment@muhs.com
*You can submit by mailing to: Attn: Registrar, 1801 East Fir Street, Cottonwood, AZ 86326
*You can submit by dropping in our drop-box located in the front horseshoe parking lot.

Once you have submitted your information, we will contact you if we have any questions, otherwise you are ready to go as a Mingus Marauder for 2020–2021 school year.

post_text: As you may be aware, Governor Ducey announced that Arizona schools must delay the start of in-person classes until August 17, 2020. As we adjust school calendars and prepare for the reopening of our campus for the 2020–2021 school year, we will do what is best for our students, families, staff, and communities. For more information, please see the intent to return to learn letter to our MUHS families from Superintendent Mike Westcott.

post_text:
Hello Mingus Families,

We look forward to welcoming you back for the 2020-21 school year! With safety, choice, and the Mingus vision in mind, we are pleased to announce our initial school-reopening plan. Our initial plan includes two excellent learning possibilities for our students: in-person learning and remote learning.

These plans are subject to change in response to community spread of the COVID-19 virus. Final plans will be made available to families by Monday, July 20th. You can find more information on our website at www.mingusunion.com

Thank you!

MUHS summer athletic/activity participation is cancelled until further notice. This decision was based off the current status of the outbreaks in our State, Yavapai County and Community.

Hello Parents and Guardians of the Class of 2020!

We need your help! We are working on our Senior Honor’s recognition and need to know what your student’s final plans are for after graduation and any awards/scholarships/recognition that they have received at this point.

We need this information by Sunday, May 17th so that we can begin working on our brochure and certificates. Please have your student provide the most complete information in the Google Form attached to this e-mail so that they receive the recognition they so deserve.

https://forms.gle/WGqvSP8V7UW9WgLz7

You can submit the information you know at this point and then re-submit new information as pending scholarships are awarded

Reach out if you have any questions.

Congratulations to the Navy Narwhals for all you have accomplished!

Gretchen Wesbrock

Director of Student Support Services

post_text: Reminder your Grade Improvement Module Packets are DUE tomorrow morning Monday May 4th by 7am!!! Get them turned in early to improve your grade!! #MUHS #Marauders
shared_text:
Mingus Union High School
April 29 at 5:34 PM ·

The Drop Box is HERE!

The Grade Improvement Module Packet drop box has been installed and is ready for packets! The box is located in the small u-shaped parking lot off of Fir Street. It is located right behind the fence on the side of the parking lot near the marquee. You will need to reach through the fence to place the packet(s) in the box. The box looks like a large postal box and is labeled with a sign “Grade Improvement Module Packet Drop-Off HERE.”

Before dropping off your packet make sure to have your student write the following:

Student Name

Student ID#

Teacher Name

These three things are very important to make sure that your student gets credit for the work they have completed.

Packets are due by Monday, May 4th at 7am.

Please reach out if you have any questions.

post_text: It's Friday night . . . Turn on your porch lights and "Be the Light" in honor of the Senior Class of 2020!!! #MUHS #SENIORS #CLASSOF2020 #ShineBright
shared_text:
Mingus Union High School
April 14 at 6:58 AM ·

As a special symbol of hope and solidarity for our Mingus seniors, Mingus Union High School will be participating in the "Be the Light" movement to honor our graduating class.
🌟
Every Friday night, beginning April 17th through May 22nd, the Mingus football stadium lights will be turned on at 8:20pm (20:20 military time) and left on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds.
🌟
This is a tribute to our Mingus graduating class of 2020 and we ask that our Mingus families and community members turn on their porch lights during this time to honor our seniors as well.
🌟
We may be physically separated, but we are emotionally connected and we hope that this will give our seniors reason to smile and feel comforted knowing their school and community is thinking about them.

Mingus Track XC
April 3 at 10:36 AM ·

Andrew Peterson
PR's:
Pole Vault - 13'6
High Jump - 6'2
Triple Jump - 35'4
Long Jump - 18' 3.25
Plans after high school: To study marketing and advertising and to start his own business
Extracurricular Activities: Mingus Swim, lifting weights, dirt biking, and working on his business
Favorite Track Memories: High jumping with his friend Jonathan freshman and sophomore year, and pole vaulting at his last meet with his friends Grant and Payson.
A few words from Andrew: "Thank you to all my family and friends who stood by my side no matter what. Whether I was crying after no heighting at state or winning medals in the pole vault, they were always there to support and encourage me."
Andrew's Senior Quote: "Strength does not come from winning. Your struggles develop your strengths. When you go through hardships and decide not to surrender, that is strength." -Arnold Schwarzenegger

shared_text:
Mingus Softball
April 14 at 6:03 AM ·

Senior spotlight:
Makayla Brogdon
Although she missed a large part of her softball career, due to a shoulder injury and then surgery, Makayla has been a part of Mingus softball for the last four years.
As a pitcher primarily, she has made appearances at the varsity level, mostly at tournaments, but this was her first season as a full time varsity player.
She shined! In our first tournament she smashed multiple homeruns and played first base, accounting for many outs for us there.
Although a quiet and laid back kid, she has an inner fire that shows in her work ethics in and off the field. She can often be found working out, running or pitching at a field somewhere or hitting in her own back yard. Although the 2020 season came to an abrupt end, she’s not finished yet...
Makayla earned her varsity letter and will be missed in our program. Once this “quarantine” passes, we will celebrate her career at Mingus and watch her walk the bases with her family! But for now, a senior picture to celebrate a cool kid and a Mingus Senior!

post_text: Don't forget starting TONIGHT and every Friday until May 22 the stadium lights will be shining bright at 8:20pm (20:20 military time) for 20 minutes and 20 seconds. All are invited to turn on your porch lights and join us in honor for our Seniors CLASS OF 2020!!! #MUHS #Seniors #BetheLIght #ShineBright #Classof2020 #MaruarderStrong
shared_text:
Mingus Union High School
April 14 at 6:58 AM ·

As a special symbol of hope and solidarity for our Mingus seniors, Mingus Union High School will be participating in the "Be the Light" movement to honor our graduating class.
🌟
Every Friday night, beginning April 17th through May 22nd, the Mingus football stadium lights will be turned on at 8:20pm (20:20 military time) and left on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds.
🌟
This is a tribute to our Mingus graduating class of 2020 and we ask that our Mingus families and community members turn on their porch lights during this time to honor our seniors as well.
🌟
We may be physically separated, but we are emotionally connected and we hope that this will give our seniors reason to smile and feel comforted knowing their school and community is thinking about them.

Our MUHS student council senior Emma Warner along with junior Rafael Fimbres, FFA Officer put together a quaranteen challenge! Please read the rules below and post with the hashtag #cwquaranteen.
*
The challenge begins today Monday April 13 and will run through the Wednesday, April 22nd!! Be creative for a chance to win a gift card!! The winner will be announced on Friday, April 24th!

Rules:

#2: Be creative (ex. TikTok, cooking, playing with goat)

#4: Must tag 2 or more friends
#5: Have fun but social distance

post_text:
** Virtual Event **
Join us for a virtual walk to #StayHealthy!
- Saturday, April 4, 2020 -

A virtual walk can be walked from any location you choose. You can walk in your neighborhood, on the trail, on the treadmill, or anywhere. You get to walk at your own pace in your own place! Bring your family or friends along, just keep it under 10 people (per CDC guidelines).

Be sure to capture the moment and tag your pictures and posts with #StayHealthy and @MATFORCEAZ when posting to your social media accounts. #MARAUDERS #StayHealthy #MATFORCEAZ #SocialDistancing

post_text:
FREE Library Access

Here is a link to the Cottonwood Public Library’s collection of ebooks and audiobooks.

https://yln.overdrive.com/

It’s FREE! All you need is a library card. If you don’t have a free library card, all you need to do is bring a bill that has your physical mailing address on it to the public library.

When you go to the website, you will need to sign in with your library card number and your PIN. Your PIN is the last 4 digits in your phone number.

---

Welcome to Mingus Union High School Remote Learning Resource.

Teachers and Staff have been working diligently adding new content for students and families in google folders. Google folders can be found on the Mingus Union High School website at www.mingusunion.com under the Learning Resources Folders tab https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/18pjYNisdSTgTYK-u-sKU_m8VY7oWJSNK

If you have any challenges with access to technology or the internet, please call 928-634-7531 and use the directory to leave a message for your Advisory teacher.

Please remember to stay home, stay safe, and wash your hands often!

Thank you for your continued support
